The Price and Accessibility of Elder Care
Services in Princess Anne, MD

00:00:06.270 --> 00:00:11.269
The number 1 aim of almost all families is
to support their dear ones reside in their

00:00:11.269 --> 00:00:15.739
own home in a safe and sound and comfortable
surrounding for as long as possible.

00:00:15.739 --> 00:00:21.470
No one’s favorite option is to go to a facility
or an institution no matter how beautiful

00:00:21.470 --> 00:00:23.949
the structure or the decorations.

00:00:23.949 --> 00:00:28.320
For a senior to live in their own house in
safety they many need just a handful of hours

00:00:28.320 --> 00:00:31.539
of services or they could need around the
clock care.

00:00:31.539 --> 00:00:36.390
An evaluation by a home care professional
is needed to identify what is best.

00:00:36.390 --> 00:00:42.520
UNDERSTANDING THE COST OF ELDER CARE SERVICES:
According to the MetLife Mature Market Annual

00:00:42.520 --> 00:00:47.530
Survey on the Cost of Care in the United States,
the findings look like this:

00:00:47.530 --> 00:00:52.719
• The national average daily rate for a
private room in a nursing home rose 4.4% from

00:00:52.719 --> 00:00:58.530
$229 in 2010 to $239 in 2011.

00:00:58.530 --> 00:01:03.649
• The national average monthly base rate
in an assisted living community rose 5.6%

00:01:03.649 --> 00:01:10.970
from $3,293 in 2010 to $3,477 in 2011.

00:01:10.970 --> 00:01:18.250
• The national average daily rate for adult
day services rose 4.5% from $67 in 2010 to

00:01:18.250 --> 00:01:20.770
$70 in 2011.

00:01:20.770 --> 00:01:26.360
• The national average hourly rates for
home health aides ($21) and homemakers ($19)

00:01:26.360 --> 00:01:29.290
were unchanged from 2010.

